# Data Layer Conventions

## Golden Rule
**All Supabase access must go through `src/store.ts`.** Never import or call `supabase` directly from a component or page.

## Supabase Tables
| Table | Entity |
|-------|--------|
| `daily_tasks` | DailyTask |
| `habits` | Habit |
| `expenses` | Expense |
| `exercise_logs` | ExerciseLog |
| `office_tasks` | OfficeTask |

## store.ts Conventions
- Each entity has its own CRUD functions in `store.ts`
- DB columns are `snake_case`; map them to `camelCase` TypeScript interfaces
- Row mappers live in `store.ts`, not in components
- Pure helpers (`computeTaskStreak`, `computeStreak`, `today`, `generateId`) also live here

## Adding a New Entity
```ts
// 1. Add type to src/types.ts
// 2. Add fetch/create/update/delete functions to src/store.ts
// 3. Map snake_case → camelCase in a row mapper in store.ts
// 4. Use useQuery/useMutation in the component, NOT raw supabase calls
```

## Error Handling
```ts
// ✅ GOOD
const { data, error } = await supabase.from("daily_tasks").select("*")
if (error) {
  console.error("Failed to fetch tasks", error)
  throw error
}

// ❌ BAD — swallowing errors silently
const { data } = await supabase.from("daily_tasks").select("*")
```
